div.p:
25. HEarken all yee, who call your ſelves the Apoſtles of Chriſt:M. M. Ch. 62.
                   hath Chriſt ſent you to warre; and ſtirre up Contention;

that you ſhould fight for Temporall goods, and outward Might, and Glory? Is that your Authoritie (John 20.) when he gave you the ſword of the Spirit, did he command you to doe ſo? hath he not ſent you to declare, and proclaime his Peace, which he hath brought unto us? What will he ſay, when he ſhall ſee that your Apoſtolicall Heart hath put on Armour? and that you have ſtirred up, and provoked your worldly Kings and Princes to the ſword; and warre; and have given them free leave out of Chriſtian Liberty: ſhall he finde you thus acting in his Service; doe you as the Diſciples of Chriſt?
